A postmortem conducted today has revealed that Somali businessman Bashir Mohammed was strangled to death. The autopsy conducted by the government chief pathologist Johansen Oduor shows that Bashir was killed before his body was dumped in river Nyamindi in Kerugoya. The body was later found at the Kirinyaga level 5 hospital, where it was identified by his family over the weekend. Bashir was laid to rest this evening at the Lang&rsquo;ata cemetery.